    >
      What kinds of people preserve their pets?
    </div>
    <p>
      Lots of people who write to me ask if they are “weird” or “morbid” for
      wanting to preserve their pets or a part of their pet. I don't think so.
      The families I've come to serve have ranged greatly in age, creed, and in
      lifestyle. I've come to learn that in one way or another, most, if not all
      pet guardians have wished to hold onto their babies for just a bit longer
      if they could, or have wondered at the possibility of taxidermy
      preservation.
    </p>

