    </div>
    <p>
      When your pet passes away, you can legally pay an aftercare professional
      to preserve your pet&#39;s fur, bones, and even their entire body (as in
      the case of taxidermy and freeze dry). However, it is illegal to then sell
      said dog or cat to another party. They can be gifted, donated to a museum,
      or passed down to family or friends. If for any reason a family decides
      they can no longer keep their preserved pet, Precious Creature can accept
      them back as a donation.
    </p>

